  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Traumatic brain injury; Glasgow coma score 4-8 (motor 1-5).

          -  Hypothermia or anti-hyperthermia must be induced within 6 hours after injury.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Systolic blood pressure &lt; 90mmHg (after resuscitation)

          -  Thrombocytopenia (platelets [Plt] &lt; 50,000/mm3)

          -  Pregnancy

          -  Preexisting medical conditions of severe hepatic dysfunction, heart failure or any
             other severe organ failure

          -  Deep drunkenness
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
